Because the code is looping through all nodes i, and for each, if the condition is met (cnt[i] is odd), then we consider a[i] as a candidate for ans. So the missing condition in the for loop is checking if cnt[i] is odd. So the code should be:

for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) if (cnt[i] % 2 == 1) ans = min(ans, a[i]);

Because the code is initializing ans as 0x3f3f3f3f (a large value), then for each i where cnt[i] is odd, we take the minimal a[i].
